# =====================================================================
# claws — repository ignore rules
# =====================================================================
# Conservative by design: when in doubt, ignore. Many of these globs
# are also (defense-in-depth) covered by gitleaks hooks.
# =====================================================================

# --- Built binaries (Go) ---
# Anchored to repo root so they don't shadow cmd/claws/ source directory.
/claws
# Legacy binaries from before the clawctl→claws rename:
/clawctl
/clawctl-v1
/clawctl-v2-mar27-backup
*.exe
# Go test binaries
*.test
# Go test cache
*.out

# --- Release artifacts ---
# release/ IS tracked — binaries live in the repo so install.sh can fetch
# them from raw.githubusercontent.com without needing a GitHub Release page.
# Only ignore the per-target directories release.sh extracts during build.
/release/claws-*-linux-*/
/release/claws-*-darwin-*/
/release/checksums-sha256.txt
/dist/
/build/
*.tgz
*.zip

# --- Credentials / secrets (never commit) ---
credentials.txt
*.env
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.pem
*.key
*.crt
id_rsa
id_rsa.pub
id_ed25519
id_ed25519.pub
*.p12
*.pfx
*.jks
# OpenClaw-specific token / registry artefacts
instance.env
.port-registry
.token-registry
.access.json

# --- Local agent state (never commit a developer's ~/.openclaw) ---
.openclaw/

# --- IDE / editor noise ---
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
*.swn
*~
.project
.classpath
.settings/

# --- OS noise ---
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
ehthumbs.db

# --- Logs / scratch ---
*.log
tmp/
.tmp/
scratch/
.scratch/
.archive/

# --- Go-specific ---
# vendor/ is optional; keep it tracked if added intentionally.
# Coverage output
coverage.out
coverage.html
profile.out
# Module cache fragments
go.work
go.work.sum

# --- Docker scratch ---
.docker-build/
docker-compose.override.yml

# --- Reports / worklogs (kept locally, not for public release) ---
# Uncomment if reports/ should be excluded from public repo:
# /reports/
# /tickets/

# --- Security-sensitive design docs kept outside the public repo ---
# These cover capability-tier design / sudo grants / per-agent privilege
# elevation. Mirrored to ~/claw/workspace/private-claws-fleet/ for the
# canonical copy.
/tickets/agent-privilege-tiers-*/
/tickets/image-from-tarball-integration-*/
/tickets/image-distribution-*/
/tickets/auth-oauth-recovery-*/
/tasklist_*.md
/tasklist.md

# --- Tooling local config ---
# Personal Claude Code settings stay local (settings.json, history, etc).
# Pattern: ignore everything INSIDE .claude/ (not the dir itself) so git
# can descend, then re-include the project-shipped skills subdir.
.claude/*
.claude-memory/
!.claude/skills/
